headline: [AUTOTVM] Use opt level 3 when extracting tasks
body:
Autotvm was implicitly ignoring opt_level when extracting tasks because
pass opt_level is a thread local variable and extraction happens in a
new thread. Not having opt_level 3 causes alter op layout to not
fire, which in turn prevents tuning from finding all possible kernels.
author: tkonolige
pr_title: [AUTOTVM] Use opt level 3 when extracting tasks

headline: Add user-configurable backtrace limit
body:
A spin off of #9872, this adds an env variable `TVM_BACKTRACE_LIMIT` which can be set to an integer to limit the frames printed out on errors. This can make it easier to run interactive TVM scripts with errors since the stack traces are often long (70+ frames).

```bash
export TVM_BACKTRACE_LIMIT=5
python some_code_with_an_error.py
```

cc @tkonolige
author: driazati
pr_title: Add user-configurable backtrace limit

headline: [microNPU][3] Plan generation for the cascader
body:
The cascader creates 'Plans' which describe how
to schedule subgraphs. As part of the cascading
algorithm, it's necessary to explore a large
variety of Plans which are Pareto optimal (in
terms of memory usage and performance). This is
done by the Plan generation algorithm.

This commit adds the TensorConfig and Plan data
structures which hold information on how to schedule
the tensors/operators. Additionally, it includes
functions to calculate Pareto frontiers which are
used to cull sub-optimal Plans.

Change-Id: Ia358b2a1b29bd810df4441027752ced75812ad4e
author: mbaret
pr_title: [microNPU][5] Convert Proposals to te.Schedules

headline: [microNPU][4] Add the cascader Proposal generator
body:
The Proposal generator takes optimal Plans and combines
them to find optimal 'Proposals' - sets of disjoint
Plans that cover every Part in a CascaderGraph. It
ultimately produces a Pareto-frontier of 'optimal'

headline: BYODT plays nicely with Relay parser
body:
Previously, there were no Bring Your Own Datatypes parser tests included
in the Relay parser tests, so when the Relay parser changed recently,
BYODT's parsing broke. This change fixes the parser and adds a test to
prevent similar breakage in the future.

- BYODT datatypes now use the format "custom_<typename><bits>x<lanes>"
  rather than "custom[<typename>]<bits>x<lanes>"
author: gussmith23
pr_title: BYODT plays nicely with Relay parser
